261
00:17:57,036 --> 00:17:59,195
Boss, please...

262
00:17:59,900 --> 00:18:01,741
If you're really worried about me,

263
00:18:02,147 --> 00:18:04,266
then don't call the police over here.

264
00:18:04,457 --> 00:18:06,779
I don't want my family getting involved in this.

265
00:18:17,100 --> 00:18:18,646
I'm sorry, Satoru.

266
00:18:19,039 --> 00:18:22,179
Nah, it's no big deal. I got to sleep a bit,

267
00:18:22,396 --> 00:18:25,207
so thanks for letting me stay and conk out on your floor.

268
00:18:25,546 --> 00:18:28,449
No, don't mention it. I just wish you could go back.

269
00:18:28,584 --> 00:18:31,032
It's OK. It's better if I don't.

270
00:18:31,620 --> 00:18:34,346
By the way, that's not your parents' house, is it?

271
00:18:34,746 --> 00:18:37,583
Huh‐uh. I'm staying with my uncle and his wife.

272
00:18:37,863 --> 00:18:39,703
My town doesn't have a high school.

273
00:18:40,063 --> 00:18:42,621
It's out in the boonies, so I
had to come to the city for it.

274
00:18:43,097 --> 00:18:45,954
I asked my uncle and he said I
could stay with them in Chiba.

275
00:18:47,444 --> 00:18:49,451
Mind if I ask a weird question?

276
00:18:49,831 --> 00:18:50,518
Hmm‐mm.

277
00:18:51,264 --> 00:18:55,181
Like, why do you believe me? You
don't even know me all that well.

278
00:18:56,729 --> 00:18:58,871
You're right, I don't, but I don't care.

279
00:18:59,172 --> 00:19:00,662
I want to believe you.

280
00:19:02,239 --> 00:19:04,066
<i>When I was in elementary school,</i>

281
00:19:04,364 --> 00:19:06,777
<i>my dad took me grocery shopping one day.</i>

282
00:19:10,504 --> 00:19:14,251
<i>The owner stopped my dad and
accused him of stealing a candy bar.</i>

283
00:19:14,804 --> 00:19:17,596
<i>Like I said, my town's small, so the owner knew my dad.</i>

284
00:19:17,942 --> 00:19:20,791
<i>He said if he just admitted
stealing it, he'd drop the whole thing.</i>

285
00:19:21,311 --> 00:19:23,865
<i>But he refused, and the owner kept pushing him.</i>

286
00:19:24,832 --> 00:19:26,871
<i>I never heard my dad yell before,</i>

287
00:19:27,038 --> 00:19:28,918
<i>but that day he went off.</i>

288
00:19:29,881 --> 00:19:31,958
<i>The owner ended up calling the police.</i>

289
00:19:32,147 --> 00:19:34,794
<i>And since my dad belonged to the local farmers' co‐op,</i>

290
00:19:35,120 --> 00:19:37,879
<i>they gave him a three‐month suspension as punishment.</i>

291
00:19:38,483 --> 00:19:42,795
You didn't steal it, Daddy. I know!
I saw, you didn't do anything wrong!

292
00:19:43,741 --> 00:19:46,593
<i>After what happened, Dad quit the co‐op,</i>

293
00:19:46,663 --> 00:19:48,738
<i>divorced Mom, and left.</i>

294
00:19:49,713 --> 00:19:51,993
<i>I guess my Mom thought he really stole it.</i>

295
00:19:52,373 --> 00:19:53,961
<i>Like everyone else in town.</i>

296
00:19:57,000 --> 00:19:59,745
If someone believes in you, you're not alone.

297
00:20:00,117 --> 00:20:03,676
And if I was in your situation,
I'd want someone to believe me.

298
00:20:05,164 --> 00:20:06,564
I think you should go home.

299
00:20:06,737 --> 00:20:09,954
Tell the cops I forced you to
hide me. They'll buy that story.

300
00:20:10,161 --> 00:20:13,446
God, you're an idiot. You
can't deal with this on your own.

301
00:20:13,544 --> 00:20:15,145
And I won't lie to the police.

302
00:20:15,226 --> 00:20:19,080
OK, but could you not call me an idiot anymore?

303
00:20:19,180 --> 00:20:20,758
No promises!

304
00:20:21,901 --> 00:20:24,645
I'll be back in a sec with a
change of clothes and stuff for you.

305
00:20:28,234 --> 00:20:31,485
<i>The boss didn't call the police after all. Good for him.</i>

306
00:20:39,626 --> 00:20:40,352
But...

307
00:20:40,924 --> 00:20:42,057
it can't be.

308
00:20:43,877 --> 00:20:45,350
What is this?

309
00:20:45,703 --> 00:20:48,889
It can't be from him 'cause he
told me his mom's phone was gone.

310
00:20:49,305 --> 00:20:50,662
Unless he found it.

311
00:20:50,998 --> 00:20:53,156
<i>No, it's from the killer.</i>

312
00:20:53,777 --> 00:20:55,015
<i>He's after me now.</i>

313
00:20:59,068 --> 00:21:01,172
Oh, my God!

314
00:21:03,427 --> 00:21:04,502
Gotta get out!

